{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":602,"text":"The first patient to ever be \ntreated with an antibiotic"},{"time":4160,"text":"was a policeman in Oxford."},{"time":5693,"text":"On his day off from work,"},{"time":7800,"text":"he was scratched by a rose thorn\nwhile working in the garden."},{"time":11173,"text":"That small scratch became infected."},{"time":14848,"text":"Over the next few days, \nhis head was swollen"},{"time":17163,"text":"with abscesses,"},{"time":18884,"text":"and in fact his eye was so infected"},{"time":21167,"text":"that they had to take it out,"},{"time":23070,"text":"and by February of 1941,"},{"time":26050,"text":"this poor man was on the verge of dying."},{"time":28487,"text":"He was at Radcliffe Infirmary in Oxford,"},{"time":31685,"text":"and fortunately for him,"},{"time":33991,"text":"a small team of doctors"},{"time":35041,"text":"led by a Dr. Howard Florey"},{"time":36930,"text":"had managed to synthesize"},{"time":38997,"text":"a very small amount of penicillin,"},{"time":41820,"text":"a drug that had been discovered"},{"time":43901,"text":"12 years before by Alexander Fleming"},{"time":46223,"text":"but had never actually been \nused to treat a human,"},{"time":49930,"text":"and indeed no one even \nknew if the drug would work,"},{"time":52340,"text":"if it was full of impurities \nthat would kill the patient,"},{"time":55980,"text":"but Florey and his team figured"},{"time":57894,"text":"if they had to use it, \nthey might as well use it"},{"time":59616,"text":"on someone who was going to die anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62181,"text":"So they gave Albert Alexander,"},{"time":65836,"text":"this Oxford policeman, the drug,"},{"time":68715,"text":"and within 24 hours,"},{"time":71132,"text":"he started getting better."},{"time":73394,"text":"His fever went down, \nhis appetite came back."},{"time":77370,"text":"Second day, he was doing much better."},{"time":79683,"text":"They were starting to \nrun out of penicillin,"},{"time":81921,"text":"so what they would do \nwas run with his urine"},{"time":83983,"text":"across the road to re-synthesize \nthe penicillin from his urine"},{"time":86833,"text":"and give it back to him,"},{"time":88768,"text":"and that worked."},{"time":90016,"text":"Day four, well on the way to recovery."},{"time":92496,"text":"This was a miracle."},{"time":94134,"text":"Day five, they ran out of penicillin,"},{"time":98370,"text":"and the poor man died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100637,"text":"So that story didn't end that well,"},{"time":103350,"text":"but fortunately for \nmillions of other people,"},{"time":107700,"text":"like this child who was treated \nagain in the early 1940s,"},{"time":110706,"text":"who was again dying of a sepsis,"},{"time":113740,"text":"and within just six days, you can see,"},{"time":116890,"text":"recovered thanks to this \nwonder drug, penicillin."},{"time":120243,"text":"Millions have lived,"},{"time":122201,"text":"and global health has been transformed."},{"time":125785,"text":"Now, antibiotics have been used"},{"time":128578,"text":"for patients like this,"},{"time":131705,"text":"but they've also been \nused rather frivolously"},{"time":133842,"text":"in some instances,"},{"time":135586,"text":"for treating someone \nwith just a cold or the flu,"},{"time":137949,"text":"which they might not have \nresponded to an antibiotic,"},{"time":140423,"text":"and they've also been \nused in large quantities"},{"time":144161,"text":"sub-therapeutically, which\nmeans in small concentrations,"},{"time":147803,"text":"to make chicken and hogs grow faster."},{"time":150986,"text":"Just to save a few pennies\non the price of meat,"},{"time":154552,"text":"we've spent a lot of \nantibiotics on animals,"},{"time":157252,"text":"not for treatment, not for sick animals,"},{"time":159614,"text":"but primarily for growth promotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162730,"text":"Now, what did that lead us to?"},{"time":165587,"text":"Basically, the massive use of antibiotics"},{"time":168298,"text":"around the world"},{"time":169783,"text":"has imposed such large\nselection pressure on bacteria"},{"time":173587,"text":"that resistance is now a problem,"},{"time":176240,"text":"because we've now selected for just"},{"time":178010,"text":"the resistant bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179985,"text":"And I'm sure you've all read\nabout this in the newspapers,"},{"time":182825,"text":"you've seen this in every magazine"},{"time":184629,"text":"that you come across,"},{"time":186528,"text":"but I really want you to appreciate"},{"time":188328,"text":"the significance of this problem."},{"time":190499,"text":"This is serious."},{"time":191950,"text":"The next slide I'm about to show you is \nof carbapenem resistance in acinetobacter."},{"time":196766,"text":"Acinetobacter is a nasty hospital bug,"},{"time":199154,"text":"and carbapenem is pretty much"},{"time":200487,"text":"the strongest class of antibiotics"},{"time":202265,"text":"that we can throw at this bug."},{"time":204721,"text":"And you can see in 1999"},{"time":207990,"text":"this is the pattern of resistance,"},{"time":210185,"text":"mostly under about 10 percent\nacross the United States."},{"time":213218,"text":"Now watch what happens \nwhen we play the video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226461,"text":"So I don't know where you live,"},{"time":228516,"text":"but wherever it is, it certainly is a lot worse now"},{"time":231418,"text":"than it was in 1999,"},{"time":233915,"text":"and that is the problem of antibiotic resistance."},{"time":237886,"text":"It's a global issue"},{"time":239573,"text":"affecting both rich and poor countries,"},{"time":242001,"text":"and at the heart of it, \nyou might say, well,"},{"time":244242,"text":"isn't this really just a medical issue?"},{"time":246170,"text":"If we taught doctors how not \nto use antibiotics as much,"},{"time":248731,"text":"if we taught patients how \nnot to demand antibiotics,"},{"time":251676,"text":"perhaps this really wouldn't be an issue,"},{"time":253131,"text":"and maybe the pharmaceutical companies"},{"time":255120,"text":"should be working harder to develop"},{"time":256875,"text":"more antibiotics."},{"time":258511,"text":"Now, it turns out that there's something \nfundamental about antibiotics"},{"time":261890,"text":"which makes it different from other drugs,"},{"time":263673,"text":"which is that if I misuse antibiotics"},{"time":265694,"text":"or I use antibiotics,"},{"time":267431,"text":"not only am I affected but \nothers are affected as well,"},{"time":271291,"text":"in the same way as if I \nchoose to drive to work"},{"time":273629,"text":"or take a plane to go somewhere,"},{"time":276268,"text":"that the costs I impose on others"},{"time":278242,"text":"through global climate change go everywhere,"},{"time":280682,"text":"and I don't necessarily take\nthese costs into consideration."},{"time":283455,"text":"This is what economists might \ncall a problem of the commons,"},{"time":286334,"text":"and the problem of the commons is exactly"},{"time":288314,"text":"what we face in the case \nof antibiotics as well:"},{"time":290739,"text":"that we don't consider —"},{"time":292889,"text":"and we, including individuals, patients,"},{"time":295891,"text":"hospitals, entire health systems —"},{"time":299050,"text":"do not consider the costs \nthat they impose on others"},{"time":301198,"text":"by the way antibiotics are actually used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303554,"text":"Now, that's a problem that's similar"},{"time":305959,"text":"to another area that we all know about,"},{"time":307941,"text":"which is of fuel use and energy,"},{"time":309870,"text":"and of course energy use"},{"time":311369,"text":"both depletes energy as well as"},{"time":314451,"text":"leads to local pollution \nand climate change."},{"time":317713,"text":"And typically, in the case of energy,"},{"time":319523,"text":"there are two ways in which\nyou can deal with the problem."},{"time":321831,"text":"One is, we can make better\nuse of the oil that we have,"},{"time":325576,"text":"and that's analogous to making better use"},{"time":327691,"text":"of existing antibiotics,"},{"time":329239,"text":"and we can do this in a number of ways"},{"time":330930,"text":"that we'll talk about in a second,"},{"time":333160,"text":"but the other option is the \n\"drill, baby, drill\" option,"},{"time":336847,"text":"which in the case of antibiotics \nis to go find new antibiotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341050,"text":"Now, these are not separate."},{"time":343100,"text":"They're related, because if we invest heavily"},{"time":346522,"text":"in new oil wells,"},{"time":348806,"text":"we reduce the incentives \nfor conservation of oil"},{"time":351760,"text":"in the same way that's going \nto happen for antibiotics."},{"time":354286,"text":"The reverse is also going \nto happen, which is that"},{"time":356454,"text":"if we use our antibiotics appropriately,"},{"time":358792,"text":"we don't necessarily have \nto make the investments"},{"time":361573,"text":"in new drug development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363750,"text":"And if you thought that these two were entirely,"},{"time":366466,"text":"fully balanced between these two options,"},{"time":368288,"text":"you might consider the fact that"},{"time":370471,"text":"this is really a game that we're playing."},{"time":372743,"text":"The game is really one of coevolution,"},{"time":375184,"text":"and coevolution is, in \nthis particular picture,"},{"time":378116,"text":"between cheetahs and gazelles."},{"time":380472,"text":"Cheetahs have evolved to run faster,"},{"time":382090,"text":"because if they didn't run faster,"},{"time":383667,"text":"they wouldn't get any lunch."},{"time":385613,"text":"Gazelles have evolved to run faster because"},{"time":388300,"text":"if they don't run faster, they would be lunch."},{"time":391509,"text":"Now, this is the game we're\nplaying against the bacteria,"},{"time":394395,"text":"except we're not the cheetahs,"},{"time":396452,"text":"we're the gazelles,"},{"time":397929,"text":"and the bacteria would,"},{"time":400716,"text":"just in the course of this little talk,"},{"time":402549,"text":"would have had kids and grandkids"},{"time":403975,"text":"and figured out how to be resistant"},{"time":406360,"text":"just by selection and trial and error,"},{"time":408834,"text":"trying it over and over again."},{"time":410746,"text":"Whereas how do we stay \nahead of the bacteria?"},{"time":414518,"text":"We have drug discovery processes,"},{"time":416572,"text":"screening molecules,"},{"time":418202,"text":"we have clinical trials,"},{"time":419930,"text":"and then, when we think we have a drug,"},{"time":422078,"text":"then we have the FDA regulatory process."},{"time":425823,"text":"And once we go through all of that,"},{"time":428001,"text":"then we try to stay one step ahead"},{"time":430266,"text":"of the bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432562,"text":"Now, this is clearly not a \ngame that can be sustained,"},{"time":435339,"text":"or one that we can win"},{"time":436476,"text":"by simply innovating to stay ahead."},{"time":438313,"text":"We've got to slow the pace of coevolution down,"},{"time":441618,"text":"and there are ideas that we \ncan borrow from energy"},{"time":445300,"text":"that are helpful in thinking about"},{"time":447070,"text":"how we might want to do this in the case"},{"time":448607,"text":"of antibiotics as well."},{"time":450153,"text":"Now, if you think about how we deal with"},{"time":452393,"text":"energy pricing, for instance,"},{"time":453816,"text":"we consider emissions taxes,"},{"time":455665,"text":"which means we're imposing \nthe costs of pollution"},{"time":458249,"text":"on people who actually use that energy."},{"time":461080,"text":"We might consider doing that for antibiotics as well,"},{"time":464060,"text":"and perhaps that would make sure that antibiotics"},{"time":466771,"text":"actually get used appropriately."},{"time":469172,"text":"There are clean energy subsidies,"},{"time":471200,"text":"which are to switch to fuels\nwhich don't pollute as much"},{"time":474255,"text":"or perhaps don't need fossil fuels."},{"time":477100,"text":"Now, the analogy here is, perhaps we need"},{"time":479960,"text":"to move away from using antibiotics,"},{"time":482220,"text":"and if you think about it, what are \ngood substitutes for antibiotics?"},{"time":485936,"text":"Well, turns out that anything that reduces"},{"time":488100,"text":"the need for the antibiotic would really work,"},{"time":490343,"text":"so that could include improving\nhospital infection control"},{"time":493485,"text":"or vaccinating people,"},{"time":496380,"text":"particularly against \nthe seasonal influenza."},{"time":498677,"text":"And the seasonal flu is probably"},{"time":501208,"text":"the biggest driver of antibiotic use,"},{"time":504212,"text":"both in this country as well\nas in many other countries,"},{"time":507131,"text":"and that could really help."},{"time":509151,"text":"A third option might include\nsomething like tradeable permits."},{"time":513254,"text":"And these seem like faraway scenarios,"},{"time":517500,"text":"but if you consider the \nfact that we might not"},{"time":519927,"text":"have antibiotics for many \npeople who have infections,"},{"time":523310,"text":"we might consider the fact that we might"},{"time":525547,"text":"want to allocate who actually gets to use"},{"time":527858,"text":"some of these antibiotics over others,"},{"time":530572,"text":"and some of these might have to\nbe on the basis of clinical need,"},{"time":533898,"text":"but also on the basis of pricing."},{"time":535833,"text":"And certainly consumer education works."},{"time":537743,"text":"Very often, people overuse antibiotics"},{"time":540344,"text":"or prescribe too much without necessarily"},{"time":542621,"text":"knowing that they do so,"},{"time":544227,"text":"and feedback mechanisms"},{"time":545658,"text":"have been found to be useful,"},{"time":547560,"text":"both on energy —"},{"time":549489,"text":"When you tell someone that they're using"},{"time":551029,"text":"a lot of energy during peak hour,"},{"time":552946,"text":"they tend to cut back,"},{"time":554416,"text":"and the same sort of example has been performed"},{"time":556183,"text":"even in the case of antibiotics."},{"time":557993,"text":"A hospital in St. Louis basically would put up"},{"time":559974,"text":"on a chart the names of surgeons"},{"time":564166,"text":"in the ordering of how much antibiotics they'd used"},{"time":566385,"text":"in the previous month,"},{"time":568329,"text":"and this was purely an \ninformational feedback,"},{"time":570671,"text":"there was no shaming,"},{"time":571854,"text":"but essentially that provided \nsome information back"},{"time":573989,"text":"to surgeons that maybe they could rethink"},{"time":575943,"text":"how they were using antibiotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578172,"text":"Now, there's a lot that can be done"},{"time":580186,"text":"on the supply side as well."},{"time":582335,"text":"If you look at the price of penicillin,"},{"time":584112,"text":"the cost per day is about 10 cents."},{"time":585763,"text":"It's a fairly cheap drug."},{"time":587521,"text":"If you take drugs that have\nbeen introduced since then —"},{"time":589658,"text":"linezolid or daptomycin —"},{"time":592302,"text":"those are significantly more expensive,"},{"time":594180,"text":"so to a world that has been used to\npaying 10 cents a day for antibiotics,"},{"time":599633,"text":"the idea of paying 180 dollars per day"},{"time":602163,"text":"seems like a lot."},{"time":603730,"text":"But what is that really telling us?"},{"time":605717,"text":"That price is telling us"},{"time":607682,"text":"that we should no longer"},{"time":609580,"text":"take cheap, effective \nantibiotics as a given"},{"time":613697,"text":"into the foreseeable future,"},{"time":615464,"text":"and that price is a signal to us"},{"time":617994,"text":"that perhaps we need to be paying"},{"time":619603,"text":"much more attention to conservation."},{"time":622156,"text":"That price is also a signal"},{"time":624860,"text":"that maybe we need to start\nlooking at other technologies,"},{"time":627735,"text":"in the same way that \ngasoline prices are a signal"},{"time":630387,"text":"and an impetus, to, say,"},{"time":632977,"text":"the development of electric cars."},{"time":634845,"text":"Prices are important signals"},{"time":636622,"text":"and we need to pay attention,"},{"time":638208,"text":"but we also need to consider the fact that"},{"time":640660,"text":"although these high prices\nseem unusual for antibiotics,"},{"time":644912,"text":"they're nothing compared to the price per day"},{"time":647151,"text":"of some cancer drugs,"},{"time":648535,"text":"which might save a patient's life only\nfor a few months or perhaps a year,"},{"time":651905,"text":"whereas antibiotics would potentially"},{"time":653675,"text":"save a patient's life forever."},{"time":655501,"text":"So this is going to involve"},{"time":656820,"text":"a whole new paradigm shift,"},{"time":658782,"text":"and it's also a scary shift because"},{"time":660638,"text":"in many parts of this country,"},{"time":662967,"text":"in many parts of the world,"},{"time":664711,"text":"the idea of paying 200 dollars"},{"time":666780,"text":"for a day of antibiotic treatment"},{"time":669671,"text":"is simply unimaginable."},{"time":672213,"text":"So we need to think about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673947,"text":"Now, there are backstop options,"},{"time":675760,"text":"which is other alternative technologies"},{"time":678436,"text":"that people are working on."},{"time":679630,"text":"It includes bacteriophages, probiotics,"},{"time":682282,"text":"quorum sensing, synbiotics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686330,"text":"Now, all of these are useful avenues to pursue,"},{"time":689369,"text":"and they will become even more lucrative"},{"time":691979,"text":"when the price of new \nantibiotics starts going higher,"},{"time":695060,"text":"and we've seen that the\nmarket does actually respond,"},{"time":697957,"text":"and the government is now considering"},{"time":699965,"text":"ways of subsidizing new \nantibiotics and development."},{"time":703732,"text":"But there are challenges here."},{"time":705455,"text":"We don't want to just throw money at a problem."},{"time":707030,"text":"What we want to be able to do"},{"time":708549,"text":"is invest in new antibiotics"},{"time":710828,"text":"in ways that actually encourage"},{"time":713804,"text":"appropriate use and sales of those antibiotics,"},{"time":716824,"text":"and that really is the challenge here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719287,"text":"Now, going back to these technologies,"},{"time":721616,"text":"you all remember the line from that famous"},{"time":723979,"text":"dinosaur film, \"Nature will find a way.\""},{"time":726205,"text":"So it's not as if these are \npermanent solutions."},{"time":729524,"text":"We really have to remember that,\nwhatever the technology might be,"},{"time":733610,"text":"that nature will find some \nway to work around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736486,"text":"You might think, well, \nthis is just a problem"},{"time":738557,"text":"just with antibiotics and with bacteria,"},{"time":741301,"text":"but it turns out that we \nhave the exact same"},{"time":743247,"text":"identical problem in \nmany other fields as well,"},{"time":745981,"text":"with multidrug-resistant tuberculosis,"},{"time":748933,"text":"which is a serious problem \nin India and South Africa."},{"time":752495,"text":"Thousands of patients are dying because"},{"time":754282,"text":"the second-line drugs are so expensive,"},{"time":756116,"text":"and in some instances, even those don't work"},{"time":758343,"text":"and you have XDR TB."},{"time":760413,"text":"Viruses are becoming resistant."},{"time":762224,"text":"Agricultural pests. Malaria parasites."},{"time":765390,"text":"Right now, much of the world depends on"},{"time":767173,"text":"one drug, artemisinin drugs,"},{"time":770870,"text":"essentially to treat malaria."},{"time":772826,"text":"Resistance to artemisinin has already emerged,"},{"time":775413,"text":"and if this were to become widespread,"},{"time":777767,"text":"that puts at risk"},{"time":779115,"text":"the single drug that we have to \ntreat malaria around the world"},{"time":782006,"text":"in a way that's currently \nsafe and efficacious."},{"time":785220,"text":"Mosquitos develop resistance."},{"time":787018,"text":"If you have kids, you probably \nknow about head lice,"},{"time":789255,"text":"and if you're from New York City,"},{"time":790968,"text":"I understand that the \nspecialty there is bedbugs."},{"time":793701,"text":"So those are also resistant."},{"time":795956,"text":"And we have to bring an\nexample from across the pond."},{"time":798835,"text":"Turns out that rats are \nalso resistant to poisons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801190,"text":"Now, what's common \nto all of these things is"},{"time":803891,"text":"the idea that we've had these technologies"},{"time":806597,"text":"to control nature only for \nthe last 70, 80 or 100 years"},{"time":811218,"text":"and essentially in a blink,"},{"time":814246,"text":"we have squandered our ability to control,"},{"time":816797,"text":"because we have not recognized"},{"time":819288,"text":"that natural selection and \nevolution was going to find"},{"time":822100,"text":"a way to get back,"},{"time":823274,"text":"and we need to completely rethink"},{"time":825323,"text":"how we're going to use"},{"time":827666,"text":"measures to control biological organisms,"},{"time":830760,"text":"and rethink how we incentivize"},{"time":834224,"text":"the development, introduction,"},{"time":836450,"text":"in the case of antibiotics prescription,"},{"time":839118,"text":"and use of these valuable resources."},{"time":842890,"text":"And we really now need to \nstart thinking about them"},{"time":845270,"text":"as natural resources."},{"time":847228,"text":"And so we stand at a crossroads."},{"time":849466,"text":"An option is to go through that rethinking"},{"time":852625,"text":"and carefully consider incentives"},{"time":854438,"text":"to change how we do business."},{"time":856992,"text":"The alternative is"},{"time":859253,"text":"a world in which even a blade of grass"},{"time":862336,"text":"is a potentially lethal weapon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864765,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866565,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}